social_posts.post_text: I can't wait to feel better and get back to adventures! 😥

Hey there! Sorry, it's been a little quiet  around here. I thought I'd say hello and let you know what's been going on! Bear with me it's been a little crazy. 
🥰
In October, I had a couple of strokes.
‼️
It's still crazy to say and fully grasp. I don't remember much of Halloween - Christmas. I spent the time mostly sleeping and on some pretty strong medications. About the first of the year, I finally mentally started feeling better and it's been a slow progression since then. 

I'm super thankful my hubby was able to take the reigns and do everything and be everywhere. Not only did I have to have someone with me at all times, he was responsible for taking care of the kids and the house and dinner and everything else. I honestly have no idea what would have happened without his love and support.

I've missed a lot and feel incredibly lucky to even be alive. I won't go into details, but it took multiple doctors visits and trips to the ER before I even got a diagnosis. Feel free to reach out if you want to know more. I'm sure I'll share it on the blog at some point.

So, thank you all for hanging in there. Sorry I've missed so much and I'll be posting a little more often.  This has been a hugely humbling experience and life is too short.

#stroke #strokesurvivor #stillhere #blessed #luckytobealive #thankful #family #lifeistooshort #strokes #life #blessed #humble #neardeathexperience

There's only a few more Fridays before summer, so I'm going to share a Friday series of some of our favorite places to visit with the kids and beat those summer "I'm bored" blues!
🌞
It's amazing how many indoor and outdoor activities there are and how many are FREE or super affordable. Follow along for tips and FUN!

This Friday's fun things to do on a budget is brought to you by Garden of the Gods Park.
🌞
While the park is absolutely breathtaking, make sure you also visit the Nature & Visitor Center.  You'll find free activities like the Junior Ranger program and also great adventures like the Tyke Hike.
🥾
On Wednesdays at 10AM, they have a guided nature hike for young explorers, ages 2-10 (with an adult.) You must register for the activity and cost is $5/person. You can also register for the Community Impact Grant to request the fee waived. Read more or plan your expedition at gardenofthegods.com.

Hi! Please come follow along and let me take a moment to say hello! We're a Colorado family that loves exploring the outdoors and taking trips and everyday adventures together.
🥰
We are Colorado born and raised, and we love the mountains, camping, and all the activities that go with it. We also love to travel! There are so many spots to visit in CO, so we try to share as many as we can, along with tips about how and when to visit.
🏕
From this pic, you can tell we adore Disney Parks and have been visiting since the kids were babies. Each visit has been different and wonderful and continually evolving. While it's amazing to watch the wonder in those tiny toddler eyes, I think this last trip with pre-teens was my favorite. Maybe it's just my sentimental, post-stroke brain, but there are just so many cool, big-kid things to do and ways to have them actively participate in the planning. It really let their interests shine and pulled us together as a family.
👋🏻
So, welcome! It's great to have you here. Please follow along, and if you're so inclined, say hello. We love to hear from and interact with the community. Tell us your favorite spots or dream destinations. We love learning from you!

Happy Magical Monday from the family! What are your plans for the week? We're enjoying the outdoors, packing for our next adventure, and getting back to school ready!

There's been a few new faces around here, so I wanted to take a moment to say hello! We're a born and raised Colorado family that loves the outdoors and exploring our great state and beyond. We love to camp, hike, and soak up that fresh, mountain air.
🩷
We also like to trade out the hiking boots for some sneakers and visit Disney Parks whenever we can. Each visit is special and unique and creates the most magic memories. Like this one above! This was our first trip back once I had the all clear to fly from my neurologist post the strokes! Those smiles all show how much we needed the pixie dust and how good it felt to be back and able to travel as a family again!

social_posts.post_text:
Today marks 1 year!! Oct 20, 2022 is the day I had my largest of 3 strokes! While the physical and mental recovery has been quite the ride, I'm so blessed and thankful to be here celebrating with my planDisney family and my sister this weekend. These gals, and the ones who couldn't make it, mean more to me than they know and probably don't realize how much they've helped me this last year! Hug the ones you love,  take time to savor the small moments, and live with a little extra grace and understanding. It's true that you never know what someone else is facing.
❤️
#strokesurvivor #thankful #plandisney #family

Happy Fri-Yay! Reliving the memories from last weekend at the #planDisney reunion. I wish I had taken more photos of all the faces I got to see and people I hugged, but that reel will just have to play in my head. It was such an incredible weekend with amazing people, and what a way to celebrate my recovery. Plus, I have the best sister ever! #thankful #waltdisneyworld #strokesurvivor #disney #classof2014

How long has Disney been a part of your life? What's your why?
❤️
While my mom sang me Disney lullabies as a baby, the first memories I have are of my first trip to Disneyland Resort in 1987. My favorite ride was Pirates of the Caribbean. I was enamored by the fireflies fluttering by our boat (we don't have those in CO), and in my 4-year-old excitement, I couldn't remember their name and called them fire-bees. Which we still all fondly refer to them as.
🐝
It's amazing how moments that seem so small develop into such a deep fondness. The combination of all of those special memories fills a place in my heart. The first shy hug into the soft belly of our favorite character, your first pair of ears or a twirl in your first princess dress. The first time you face your fears on Haunted Mansion or Space Mountain. The first smell of Main Street, U.S.A. or seeing fireworks. Those firsts create everlasting feelings we want to relive over and over again and then watch happen with those we love, our children and grandchildren.
💖
So there's the answer to why I always want to go back to Disney. I get those warm, fuzzy feelings, watch my kids create their own memories, and fill my cup up all over again until our next magical trip. ChEARs to 100 years and to Minnie, many more!
🏰
